# Static assets and images

- **Next.js serves static files only from the `public/` directory.** URLs like `/images/foo.png` resolve to `public/images/foo.png`.

- **Do not create symlinks, junctions, or directory links** to make project-root folders (e.g. `images/`) appear under `public/`. Do not run `mklink`, `ln -s`, or similar.

- **Instead, tell the user** to put their image (or asset) files in **`public/images/`** (or the appropriate subfolder under `public/`), e.g.:
  - "Put your champion images in `public/images/` so they are served at `/images/`. For example `public/images/Alysia.png` will be available at `/images/Alysia.png`."

- If the user already has files elsewhere (e.g. project root `images/`), instruct them to **copy or move** those files into `public/images/` rather than linking.
